{"type":"message","id":"df44af75","parentId":"a7946294","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:54:12.754Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-03-31 00:54 GMT+2] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Führe eine vollständige SICHERHEITSANALYSE des ECC Second Brain Framework Codes durch.\n\nZiel-Verzeichnis: C:\\Users\\andre\\Documents\\Andrew Openclaw\\Kimi_Agent_ECC-Second-Brain-Framework Implementiert\\\n\nAnalysiere ALLE Python-Dateien (.py) rekursiv im Verzeichnis. Konzentriere dich auf:\n\n1. **Code Execution Risks** - eval(), exec(), compile(), subprocess, os.system\n2. **File System Risks** - Path traversal, arbitrary file write/delete, unsichere Path-Konstruktion\n3. **Network Risks** - requests, urllib, unsichere Downloads, fehlende Timeouts\n4. **Deserialization Risks** - pickle, yaml.load(), unsichere json.loads()\n5. **Injection Vulnerabilities** - SQL injection, command injection, template injection\n6. **Resource Exhaustion** - Unendliche Loops, unbegrenzte Memory-Allokation\n7. **Secrets Management** - Hardcoded API keys, tokens, passwords\n\nStrukturierte Ausgabe erforderlich:\n- GESAMTRISIKO: NONE/LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH/CRITICAL\n- Pro Datei: Risiko-Level + konkrete Befunde mit Zeilennummern\n- Positive Sicherheitsmuster (was gut gemacht wurde)\n- Konkrete Empfehlungen für Verbesserungen\n\nNutze den neuen Security-Review Skill als Leitfaden."}],"timestamp":1774911252750}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac1764ea","parentId":"df44af75","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:54:28.004Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" I need to perform a comprehensive security analysis of the ECC Second Brain Framework code. Let me start by reading the Security-Review Skill to understand the best practices and methodology for this analysis.\n\nFirst, I'll read the skill file, then explore the target directory to understand its structure, and finally analyze all Python files recursively.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_ri2R5JpN80fM2mJwZBj7ixMs","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\security-review\\SKILL.md"}},{"type":"text","text":"  "}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":8498,"output":90,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8588,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774911252753}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c3f6885","parentId":"ac1764ea","timestamp":"2026-03-30T22:54:28.024Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_ri2R5JpN80fM2mJwZBj7ixMs","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: security-review\ndescription: |\n  Automated security analysis skill for Python code and repositories.\n  \n  Use WHEN: Analyzing code for security vulnerabilities, reviewing repositories\n  for security risks, auditing dependencies, or assessing execution safety.\n  \n  Trigger phrases: \"security audit\", \"analyze security\", \"security review\",\n  \"check for vulnerabilities\", \"is this code safe\", \"security analysis\",\n  \"audit repository\", \"security check\"\n\ncategory: security\ntags:\n  - security\n  - audit\n  - review\n  - vulnerability\n  - code-analysis\n\nmetadata:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  author: \"Andrew\"\n  requires: [read, write, web_fetch, web_search]\n---\n\n# Security Review Skill\n\nAutomated security analysis for Python code and repositories.\n\n## Capabilities\n\n### 1. Code Execution Risk Detection\n\nIdentifies dangerous Python functions and patterns:\n\n| Risk Category | Dangerous Patterns | Safe Alternatives |\n|--------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| Code Injection | `eval()`, `exec()`, `compile()` | `ast.literal_eval()`, parsers |\n| Command Execution | `os.system()`, `subprocess.call()` | `subprocess.run(check=False)` with validation |\n| Dynamic Import | `__import__()`, `importlib` | Static imports, whitelist |\n| Template Injection | `str.format(**locals())` | Jinja2 with sandbox |\n\n### 2. File System Risk Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ DANGEROUS - Path Traversal\nfile_path = \"/data/\" + user_input\n\n# ✅ SAFE - Path validation\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbase = Path(\"/data\").resolve()\nrequested = (base / user_input).resolve()\nif not requested.is_relative_to(base):\n    raise ValueError(\"Invalid path\")\n```\n\n### 3. Network Risk Detection\n\n| Check | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| URL Validation | Hardcoded vs. user-controlled URLs |\n| Protocol Check | HTTPS required, HTTP flagged |\n| Timeout Presence | All requests must have timeouts |\n| Domain Allowlist | External requests to approved domains only |\n\n### 4. Deserialization Risk Detection\n\n| Method | Risk Level | Safe Alternative |\n|--------|-----------|------------------|\n| `pickle.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `json.load()`, `torch.load(weights_only=True)` |\n| `yaml.load()` | 🔴 HIGH | `yaml.safe_load()` |\n| `json.load()` | 🟢 LOW | Already safe |\n\n### 5. Resource Exhaustion Detection\n\nIdentifies:\n- Unbounded loops without exit conditions\n- Memory allocation without limits\n- File operations without size checks\n- Network requests without timeouts\n\n## Risk Levels\n\n| Level | Description | Action Required |\n|-------|-------------|-----------------|\n| 🟢 NONE | No security concerns | None |\n| 🟢 LOW | Minor concerns, well-controlled | Document |\n| 🟡 MEDIUM | Moderate risk, needs attention | Review |\n| 🟠 HIGH | Significant security risk | Fix before use |\n| 🔴 CRITICAL | Immediate security threat | Do not use |\n\n## Usage\n\n### Analyze a Single File\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/file.py\"\n  checks:\n    - code_execution\n    - file_system\n    - network\n    - deserialization\n    - resources\n```\n\n### Analyze a Repository\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"https://github.com/user/repo\"\n  depth: full\n  include_dependencies: true\n```\n\n### Checklist Mode\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/project\"\n  mode: checklist\n  output_format: markdown\n```\n\n## Security Checklist\n\n### Python Code Checklist\n\n- [ ] No `eval()` or `exec()` usage\n- [ ] No `os.system()` or unvalidated `subprocess` calls\n- [ ] No dynamic `__import__()` with user input\n- [ ] All file paths validated (no traversal)\n- [ ] All network requests have timeouts\n- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or credentials\n- [ ] Pickle/yaml usage reviewed\n- [ ] No infinite loops without safeguards\n- [ ] Error messages don't leak sensitive info\n\n### Dependency Checklist\n\n- [ ] Dependencies pinned or minimum versions set\n- [ ] No known CVEs in dependencies\n- [ ] External indexes verified (PyPI vs. custom)\n- [ ] Compiled extensions from trusted sources\n\n## Analysis Report Format\n\n```markdown\n## Security Analysis: {target}\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall Risk: {LEVEL}\n- Critical Issues: {count}\n- Medium Issues: {count}\n- Low Issues: {count}\n\n### Detailed Findings\n\n#### 1. {Category} (Risk: {LEVEL})\n**Location:** {file}:{line}\n**Issue:** {description}\n**Recommendation:** {fix}\n\n### Safe Patterns Found\n- ✅ {pattern description}\n\n### Recommendations\n1. {priority recommendation}\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n### Example 1: Safe Code Pattern\n\n```python\n# ✅ GOOD - Time-bounded execution\nimport time\nMAX_RUNTIME = 300  # 5 minutes\nstart = time.time()\n\nwhile condition:\n    if time.time() - start > MAX_RUNTIME:\n        break\n    process()\n```\n\n### Example 2: Unsafe Pattern Detection\n\n```python\n# ❌ BAD - Code injection risk\ndef process_user_code(code):\n    return eval(code)  # NEVER DO THIS\n\n# ❌ BAD - Path traversal\ndef read_file(filename):\n    return open(f\"/data/{filename}\").read()\n\n# ❌ BAD - No timeout\nimport requests\nresponse = requests.get(url)  # Can hang forever\n```\n\n## References\n\n- OWASP Top 10: https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/\n- CWE/SANS Top 25: https://cwe.mitre.org/top25/\n- Python Security: https://python-security.readthedocs.io/\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774911268021}}
